    "27482971": {
      "title": "Epidural analgesia for pancreatoduodenectomy: a critical appraisal",
      "abstract": "Introduction ::: Epidural analgesia has emerged as a commonly applied method to improve pain management and reduce perioperative complications in major abdominal surgery. However, there is no detailed analysis of its efficacy for pancreatic operations. This study compares clinical and economic outcomes after epidural and intravenous analgesia for pancreatoduodenectomy."
